## 1. Technical Overview

FractionQuest is a **React Single-Page Application (SPA)** built with Vite, designed to be embedded within the existing `intelliasg.com` WordPress/LMS environment as a standalone lesson page. It is a simulation-first, audio-narrated, gamified learning experience that mirrors the architecture of the `dsamyak/equal` repository and the live reference at `equal-tau.vercel.app`.

### Technology Stack Summary

| Layer | Technology | Justification |
|-------|-----------|---------------|
| Framework | React 18 + Vite | Fast HMR, component model matches reference repo |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + CSS Variables | Matches reference repo; rapid utility styling |
| Animation | Framer Motion | Spring physics, gesture support, drag-and-drop |
| Audio | Howler.js | Reliable cross-browser audio with preloading |
| State Management | Zustand | Lightweight global state (no Redux boilerplate) |
| Routing | React Router v6 | Scene-based navigation within the SPA |
| Persistence | localStorage API | Session resume without backend |
| Testing | Vitest + React Testing Library | Unit + integration tests |
| Deployment | Vercel (preview) → intelliasg.com | Matches reference repo deployment pattern |

